<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>Web Key Directory - Tester</title>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="https://chimbosonic.com/favicon.ico">
    <style>
        table {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            {{!-- width: 100%; --}}
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        th,
        td {
            border: 1px solid #dddddd;
            text-align: left;
            padding: 12px 15px;
            vertical-align: top;
        }

        thead tr {
            background-color: #009879;
            color: #ffffff;
        }

        tbody tr {
            border-bottom: 1px solid #dddddd;
        }

        tbody tr:nth-of-type(even) {
            background-color: #f3f3f3;
        }

        tbody tr:last-of-type {
            border-bottom: 2px solid #009879;
        }
    </style>

</head>

<body>
    <h1>Web Key Directory - Tester</h1>
    <p><a href="https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-koch-openpgp-webkey-service/">OpenPGP Web Key Directory</a> is a
        key discovery scheme that allows discovering OpenPGP keys from e-mail addresses.
    <p>For example when looking up <code>Joe.Doe@example.org</code> keys would be located at: </p>
    <ul>
        <li>For the Direct Method: <p>
                <code>https://example.org/.well-known/openpgpkey/hu/iy9q119eutrkn8s1mk4r39qejnbu3n5q?l=Joe.Doe</code>
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>For the Advanced Method: <p>
                <code>https://openpgpkey.example.org/.well-known/openpgpkey/example.org/hu/iy9q119eutrkn8s1mk4r39qejnbu3n5q?l=Joe.Doe</code>
            </p>
        </li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Lookup</h2>
    <p>For testing purposes, you can use the following form to look up keys or generate the locations you need to store
        your binary formated key:</p>
    <form action="/" method="post">
        <label for="email">E-mail address:</label>
        <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
        <input type="submit" value="Lookup">
    </form>
    {{#each this}}
    <h3>Results for {{this.user_id}}</h3>
    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th></th>
                <th>Direct Method</th>
                <th>Advanced Method</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>URI:</td>
                <td>{{this.direct_method.uri}}</td>
                <td>{{this.advanced_method.uri}}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Key Fingerprint:</td>
                <td>{{this.direct_method.key.fingerprint}}</td>
                <td>{{this.advanced_method.key.fingerprint}}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Errors:</td>
                {{#each this.direct_method.errors}}
                <td>

                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Error Code</th>
                                <th>Error Message</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>

                        <tr>
                            <td>{{this.name}}</td>
                            <td>{{this.message}}</td>
                        </tr>

                    </table>
                </td>
                {{/each}}
                {{#each this.advanced_method.errors}}
                <td>
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Error Code</th>
                                <th>Error Message</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>

                        <tr>
                            <td>{{this.name}}</td>
                            <td>{{this.message}}</td>
                        </tr>

                    </table>
                </td>
                {{/each}}
            </tr>
        </tbody>
    </table>
    {{/each}}

    <h2>API Usage</h2>

    <p>There is also API that returns the same results in JSON format. For example to look up
        <code>Joe.Doe@example.org</code> using the API
    </p>
    <p>You would hit the following endpoint: <a href="/api/Joe.Doe@example.org">/api/Joe.Doe@example.org</a>. Which
        would return the following JSON:</p>
    <pre><code>
{
  "user_id": "Joe.Doe@example.org",
  "direct_method": {
    "uri": "https://example.org/.well-known/openpgpkey/hu/iy9q119eutrkn8s1mk4r39qejnbu3n5q?l=Joe.Doe",
    "key": {
      "fingerprint": "AC48BC1F029B6188D97E2D807C855DB4466DF0C6"
    },
    "errors": []
  },
  "advanced_method": {
    "uri": "https://openpgpkey.example.org/.well-known/openpgpkey/example.org/hu/iy9q119eutrkn8s1mk4r39qejnbu3n5q?l=Joe.Doe",
    "key": {
      "fingerprint": "AC48BC1F029B6188D97E2D807C855DB4466DF0C6"
    },
    "errors": []
  }
}
    </code></pre>
